race.comment: TROPIC SANDS (2) steps up in trip off narrow defeats at the track. Comes back in grade and uses an inside gate. Has strong NSW form at this distance range and is ready to win. WATERMELON (1) won this grade here by a space and was heavily backed following finding AUTUNNO too good over 1900m. Has a tricky gate but keeps the handy 3kg claim and is a decent chance to bounce. SETTAT (3) disappointed late over 1800m at Sunshine Coast after racing on the pace. He was a big 55 winner there prior and deserves another chance. AUTUNNO (4) led after a slow start in the WATERMELON race, spiking his figures. He'll be a contender holding that form. IRON GRACE (5) has been racing in town and is a better chance than the formline suggests.
